vocabulary.definition: the omission from speech or writing of a word or words that are superfluous or able to be understood from contextual clues

vocabulary.example: He delivered a powerful bismo to his opponent during the boxing match.

vocabulary.definition: a small, round mark made by or as if by pressure
vocabulary.example: The blon on the paper indicated where the seal had been pressed.
She tripped over her own feet in a moment of cluggins.

vocabulary.definition: a person who drinks alcohol excessively

vocabulary.definition: proudly displaying one's abilities, qualities, or possessions
